{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769629327,"nonce":"8miFbEAceq59crbG55aeAD3yn/Y=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mfuSx","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/106","origin":"github"},"title":"Implement git worktree-based task isolation and rename workspaces‚Üílayers","message":"## Problem Statement\n\nCurrently, the workspace uses branch-based isolation for multi-agent coordination. While effective, this has significant limitations:\n\n- **Serial Context Switching**: Only one task active per clone\n- **Build Contamination**: Switching branches requires full rebuild  \n- **State Conflicts**: Uncommitted changes must be stashed\n- **Scratchpad Collisions**: Documented in `.agent/SCRATCHPAD_COLLISION_ANALYSIS.md`\n- **ROS Environment Conflicts**: Single install/build space shared across tasks\n- **Terminology Confusion**: \"workspaces\" used for both root repo AND ROS layers\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n**Part 1**: Rename `workspaces/` ‚Üí `layers/` for clarity\n- \"Workspace\" = root `ros2_agent_workspace` repository  \n- \"Layers\" = ROS2 workspace layers (underlay, core, platforms, etc.)\n\n**Part 2**: Use **git worktrees** for isolated task environments\n\n### Architecture (Final Design)\n```\nros2_agent_workspace/           # The workspace (root repository)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .git/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .agent/                     # Shared infrastructure\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ configs/                    # Shared configs\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ layers/                     # RENAMED from workspaces/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main/                   # Main branch checkout\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ underlay_ws/\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ core_ws/\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src/\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ build/\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ install/\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ platforms_ws/\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ sensors_ws/\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ worktrees/              # Task-specific (ROS package work)\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ issue-22/\n‚îÇ       ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ underlay_ws/\n‚îÇ       ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ core_ws/\n‚îÇ       ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src/\n‚îÇ       ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ build/      # Isolated\n‚îÇ       ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ install/    # Isolated\n‚îÇ       ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ log/        # Isolated\n‚îÇ       ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ .scratchpad/    # Task-specific\n‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ issue-107/\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ .workspace-worktrees/       # For infrastructure changes\n    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ issue-104-fix-docs/     # Full workspace checkout\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ issue-108-agent-script/\n```\n\n### Two Worktree Types\n\n**Type 1: Layer Worktrees** (`layers/worktrees/issue-N/`)\n- For ROS package development\n- Isolated build/install/log per task\n- Each worktree is a separate ROS environment\n\n**Type 2: Workspace Worktrees** (`.workspace-worktrees/issue-N/`)\n- For infrastructure work (.agent/, configs/, docs)\n- Full workspace checkout\n- For parallel infrastructure development\n\n## Benefits\n\n### For AI Agents\n- ‚úÖ **True Parallel Work**: Multiple agents work simultaneously\n- ‚úÖ **Clean Handoff**: Worktree persists with all context\n- ‚úÖ **No State Management**: No stashing required\n- ‚úÖ **Isolated Environments**: Dedicated ROS environment per task\n\n### For Developers  \n- ‚úÖ **Fast Context Switching**: No rebuild needed\n- ‚úÖ **Compare Implementations**: Side-by-side testing\n- ‚úÖ **Clear Terminology**: workspace vs layers distinction\n\n### For Workspace\n- ‚úÖ **Eliminates Scratchpad Collisions**: Isolated per task\n- ‚úÖ **Prevents Build Contamination**: Isolated artifacts\n- ‚úÖ **Reduces Coordination Overhead**: No locking needed\n\n## Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 0: Rename workspaces/ ‚Üí layers/ (Foundation)\n- [ ] Update all .repos files in `configs/repos/`\n- [ ] Update all scripts in `.agent/scripts/`\n- [ ] Update Makefile\n- [ ] Update all documentation\n- [ ] Perform rename: `git mv workspaces layers`\n- [ ] Test all scripts\n- [ ] Commit as single atomic change\n\n### Phase 1: Core Worktree Infrastructure\n- [ ] `worktree_create_layer.sh` - Create layer worktree\n- [ ] `worktree_create_workspace.sh` - Create workspace worktree  \n- [ ] `worktree_enter.sh` - Enter with proper environment\n- [ ] `worktree_list.sh` - Show all active worktrees\n- [ ] `worktree_remove.sh` - Clean up\n\n### Phase 2: Build System Integration\n- [ ] Update `Makefile` for worktree-local paths\n- [ ] Update `build.sh` to detect context\n- [ ] Update `test.sh` for isolated results\n- [ ] Update `env.sh` for worktree-aware sourcing\n\n### Phase 3: Agent Integration\n- [ ] Update `start_issue_work.sh` to support worktrees\n- [ ] Update `WORKFORCE_PROTOCOL.md`\n- [ ] Update `git-hygiene.md`\n- [ ] Update `status_report.sh`\n\n### Phase 4: CLI Shortcuts\n- [ ] `/create-worktree`, `/enter-worktree`, `/list-worktrees`, `/remove-worktree`\n\n### Phase 5: Documentation\n- [ ] Create `WORKTREE_GUIDE.md`\n- [ ] Update `README.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `AI_RULES.md`\n\n### Phase 6: Testing\n- [ ] Test concurrent builds\n- [ ] Validate environment isolation\n- [ ] Test cleanup\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] Two agents can work on different issues simultaneously\n- [ ] Terminology is clear (workspace vs layers)\n- [ ] Worktree creation \u003c 30 seconds\n- [ ] Build artifacts properly isolated\n- [ ] No scratchpad collisions\n- [ ] Comprehensive documentation\n\n## Related\n\n- #103 - Workflow protocol compliance\n- `.agent/SCRATCHPAD_COLLISION_ANALYSIS.md`\n\n## Priority\n\n**High** - Enables true multi-agent parallelism, eliminates collisions, clarifies terminology.\n\n---\n**ü§ñ Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**üßÝ Model**: `Claude Sonnet 4.5`","files":null}]}